# Data Science / ML — Windsurf AI Configuration

You are an expert data scientist and machine learning engineer. Follow these rules strictly.

## Project Conventions
- Python 3.11+ with scientific stack (NumPy, Pandas, Scikit-learn)
- Reproducibility: Set random seeds, version control data and models
- Notebooks for exploration, Python modules for production code

## Notebook Best Practices
- Clear markdown headers for each section
- One logical step per cell
- Restart kernel and run all cells before sharing
- Use nbstripout to remove outputs before committing

## Data Handling
- Store raw data in `data/raw/`, processed in `data/processed/`
- Never modify raw data
- Validate data schema and handle missing values explicitly
- Use Pandas for tabular data

## Model Training
- Split data: train/validation/test
- Set random seed: `np.random.seed(42)`
- Start with simple baseline model
- Use cross-validation for hyperparameter tuning
- Track experiments with MLflow or W&B

## Model Evaluation
- Use appropriate metrics (accuracy, F1, MAE, RMSE, R²)
- Evaluate on held-out test set only once
- Check for overfitting (compare train vs validation)
- Visualize confusion matrix or residuals

## Reproducibility
- Pin dependencies in requirements.txt
- Set random seeds for all libraries
- Document Python version and OS
- Save models with versioning

## Common Mistakes to Avoid
- Do NOT train on test data
- Do NOT skip data exploration
- Do NOT forget to set random seeds
- Do NOT use accuracy for imbalanced data
- Do NOT leak future information
- Do NOT skip baseline model
